HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1335
By Terry
A RESOLUTION to commend Abigail Neeley for exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, Abigail Neeley has distinguished herself through her exceptional dedication
to public service and her commitment to excellence, as evidenced by her outstanding academic
achievement reflected in a 3.83 grade point average; and
WHEREAS, she has served as an intern in the Tennessee Legislative Internship
Program, where she has assisted Chairman Bryan Terry with legislative research, policy
analysis, and administrative support related to committee and floor activities; and
WHEREAS, in her role, she has prepared briefing materials, talking points, and
background information to support informed decision-making in legislative proceedings; and
WHEREAS, she has contributed to the effective operation of legislative committees by
organizing materials, staffing hearings, and documenting key policy discussions and outcomes;
and
WHEREAS, she has demonstrated a strong understanding of public policy by attending
legislative meetings, recording detailed notes, and summarizing complex issues and
stakeholder perspectives; and
WHEREAS, she has participated in educational visits to significant state institutions,
gaining valuable insight into the operations of Tennessee's legal and public safety systems; and
WHEREAS, she gained meaningful legal experience through her work with the
Rutherford County Public Defender's Office, where she observed courtroom proceedings and
assisted with case preparation and administrative functions; and
HJR1335
017498
- 1 -

WHEREAS, she has shown professionalism and attention to detail by coordinating with
local agencies and supporting the efficient management of legal documentation and case
materials; and
WHEREAS, she has demonstrated leadership, patience, and compassion through her
work as a teacher, where she developed lesson plans and fostered a positive learning
environment for young children; and
WHEREAS, she has exhibited a strong work ethic and sense of responsibility through
her experience in the service industry, managing customer relations, financial duties, and
operational tasks; and
WHEREAS, she has further shown her commitment to her community through volunteer
service, assisting educators and supporting classroom needs; and
WHEREAS, Abigail Neeley exemplifies the qualities of integrity, diligence, and a
steadfast commitment to serving others, making her a worthy recipient of recognition by this
General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Abigail Neeley for outstanding service as a legislative
intern for Chairman Bryan Terry and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
